The paper proposes a deep learning framework for traffic prediction that integrates various types of auxiliary information. This involves encoding offline geographical and social attributes, road intersection information, and online crowd queries. The paper also uses an encoder-decoder sequence learning framework. Based on these factors, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
